contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox mountain | name = Ta' Dmejrek | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 253 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 253 | prominence_ref = | map = Malta | map_caption = Malta | label_position = left | listing = [[List of countries by highest point|Country high point]] | location = [[Siġġiewi]], [[Malta]] | range = | lat_d = 35 | lat_m = 50 | lat_s = 45 | lat_NS = N | long_d = 14 | long_m = 23 | long_s = 47 | long_EW = E | region = MT | coordinates_ref = | topo = | type = | age = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }} '''Ta' Dmejrek''' is the highest point of [[Malta]], located on the [[Dingli|Dingli Cliffs]], with an altitude of 253 metres (830 ft).
